# =============================================================================
# JARVIS .gitignore
# Tracked: source code, docs, knowledge_base.jsonl, model_catalog.json,
#          .agent/ rules and workflows, learning materials.
# Excluded: regenerable binaries, third-party clones, large static reference.
# =============================================================================

# -- Binary regenerables (rebuild from source code + research papers) ---------
jarvis_data/chromadb/
jarvis_data/chromadb_backups/
jarvis_data/extracted_images/

# ChromaDB persistence created by learning exercises or scratch tests anywhere
# in the tree (sqlite + the UUID-named binary index dirs alongside them)
**/chroma.sqlite3*
**/demo_metadata_db/
**/test_jarvis_persistence_db/
**/*_chromadb/
**/*_chroma_db/

# -- Third-party clones (re-clone fresh on each laptop) -----------------------
# OpenClaude/ (Tracking explicitly for personal-laptop sync)
OpenJarvis/
Open-Claude-Cowork/

# -- Large static reference --------------------------------------------------
# Research papers are ~50 MB and almost never change.
# Bulk-copy them once via the HDD's jarvis-bulk/ folder, not via git.
research papers/

# -- Python ------------------------------------------------------------------
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.egg-info/
.pytest_cache/
.venv/
venv/
env/
.eggs/

# -- Node --------------------------------------------------------------------
node_modules/
*.log
npm-debug.log*

# -- Editor / IDE / OS junk --------------------------------------------------
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*~
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# -- Machine-local operational infrastructure (not part of the synced project)
# CLAUDE.md is a Claude Code @import proxy at repo root — work-laptop-only.
CLAUDE.md
# SYNC.md / RUNBOOK.md were the HDD-era operational docs — superseded by
# GitHub-based sync; kept locally on work laptop for reference.
SYNC.md
RUNBOOK.md
# .agent/ is the per-runtime workflow + rules infrastructure. Each machine
# customizes its own copy: personal laptop has the canonical Antigravity-era
# workflows (/learn, /memory, /research, etc. + always-on rules); work laptop
# has its own scratchpad version. Keeping it machine-local prevents the two
# copies from clobbering each other on pulls.
#
# EXCEPTION: .agent/workflows/next.md is tracked to synchronize
# roadmap progress enforcement across both machines. Wildcard + negation
# pattern below is required because gitignore can't re-include a file
# under a fully-excluded directory.
.agent/*
!.agent/workflows/
.agent/workflows/*
!.agent/workflows/next.md
# .claude/ is Claude Code's per-project settings dir (work-laptop-only;
# personal laptop runs Antigravity, not Claude Code). Machine-local.
.claude/

# -- Legacy / regenerable data files ----------------------------------------
# knowledge.md is the raw source distilled into Data_Engineering_Lessons.md.
# Personal laptop has its own pre-existing copy from the Antigravity-era setup.
jarvis_data/knowledge.md
# model_catalog.json is regenerable via `python3 scripts/sync_openrouter.py`.
# Snapshot goes stale anyway as OpenRouter's catalog evolves.
jarvis_data/model_catalog.json

# -- Local secrets / env -----------------------------------------------------
.env
.env.local
*.local
*.pem
*.key

# -- Build artifacts ---------------------------------------------------------
dist/
build/
*.tar.gz
*.zip

# -- Untracked local items ---------------------------------------------------
jarvis_data/openclaude_jarvis_patches.patch
Q&A/
ollama models/
